newsitem.title: ARGENTINA: Argentine October industrial output up 12.5 pct.
newsitem.headline: Argentine October industrial output up 12.5 pct.

text.p: Argentina's industrial production in October was 12.5 percent higher than in October 1995, the Economy Ministry said Monday.
The output level in October rose 4.1 percent from September and 0.9 percent on a seasonally adjusted basis.
The announcement was made only hours after the FIEL private consultancy estimated an 11.3 percent increase over October last year.
In the January-October period industrial production rose 3.2 percent over the same 1995 period, the ministry said.

"Most sectors showed an improvement in the month of October 1996 compared with the same month 1995, in particular automobiles, textiles, machinery, construction material and steel," the ministry said in its monthly report.
October was the seventh consecutive month of industrial output growth following a year-long recession induced by the "Tequila effect" of Mexico's December 1994 peso devaluation.
